      <section id="_authoring_processes_in_bamoe_canvas">
         <p>Process authoring on BAMOE Canvas happens inside the Editor page for Workflow, where you can edit and validate BPMN files.</p>
         <p>Let’s start by describing the elements present in the BPMN Editor.</p>
         <fig>
            <title>Editor page for a Workflow on BAMOE Canvas with highlighted elements of the BPMN Editor</title>
            <image href="../images/tools/image5.jpg" placement="break">
               <alt>image5</alt>
            </image>
         </fig>
         <ol>
            <li>
               <b>Node palette</b> → From here you can select node types and their variations.</li>
            <li>
               <p>
                  <b>Side panel strip</b> → Lets you select which side panel you want to toggle.
From top to bottom, those are the available panels:</p>
               <ol>
                  <li>Properties → Lets you manage the properties of a Workflow element.</li>
                  <li>Navigator → Displays a minimap with the diagram of your Workflow and a list of all elements present on it.</li>
               </ol>
            </li>
            <li>
               <b>Keyboard shortcuts panel toggle →</b> Clicking here toggles a panel with information about keyboard shortcuts available in the BPMN Editor.</li>
         </ol>
         <p>Toggling the Problems tab lets you see static validation errors that BAMOE Canvas reports while you’re developing your Workflows.</p>
         <p>Developing Workflows through BPMN files is a complex subject and has many intricacies that are beyond the scope of this document.
For more information, see BPMN-specific material, <xref href="https://www.omg.org/spec/BPMN/2.0.2/PDF" scope="external">BPMN specification</xref>.</p>
